	nobel design holdings ltd
	
Nobel Design Holdings Ltd. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 20 17
Nobel Design Holdings Ltd. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company's revenue was SGD 23,569,000 compared with SGD 21,151,000 a year ago. This increase is mainly attributable to the group's supply chain division which sells to the USA market. Profit before income tax was SGD 1,525,000 compared with SGD 1,342,000 a year ago. Profit attributable to equity holders of the company was SGD 520,000 compared with SGD 867,000 a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was SGD 3,249,000 compared with net cash used in operating activities of SGD 1,114,000 a year ago. Earnings per diluted share were 0.23 cents compared to 0.40 cents a year ago. As on March 31, 2017, the company's net asset value per share was 73.84 cents compared to 73.64 cents a year ago. The group's net profit after tax for the first quarter decreased by 39% to SGD 0.78 million as compared to a net profit after tax of SGD 1.29 million for the first quarter ended 31 March 2016. This was mainly due to a fall in the group's share of profits from its property investments joint ventures which was partially offset by the increase in contribution from the supply chain division.


Nobel Design Holdings Ltd Announces Executive Changes
Apr 18 17
The Board of Directors of Nobel Design Holdings Ltd. announced that Teh Ban Lian, who shall retire at the forthcoming Annual General Meeting of the company to be held on 28 April 2017 pursuant to Article 107 of the company's Constitution, has indicated that he will not be standing for re-election at the AGM. Concurrent with Teh's retirement as Independent Director of the Company at the AGM, he will cease to be the Chairman of the Risk Management Sub-Committee and member of the Audit and Nominating Committees with effect from the close of the AGM. In addition, Chan Kum Leong will be re-designated as an Independent Director and appointed as Chairman of the Risk Management Sub-Committee and member of the Nominating Committee in place of Teh with effect from the close of the AGM. Wong Soon Chiu will be appointed as a member of the Nominating Committee in place of Goon Eu Jin Terence who will step down as a member of the Nominating Committee with effect from the close of the AGM. Following the changes, the composition of the Board, Committees and Risk Management Sub-Committee of the company will be reconstituted as Wong Soon Chiu as Chairman of Audit Committee, Chan Pengee, Adrian as Member of Audit Committee, Heng Chye Yam as Member of Audit Committee, Chan Pengee, Adrian as Chairman of Nominating Committee, Wong Soon Chiu as Member of Nominating Committee, Chan Kum Leong as Member of Nominating Committee, Chan Kum Leong as Chairman of Risk Management Sub-Committee, Heng Chye Yam as Member of Risk Management Sub-Committee and Wong Soon Chiu as Member of Risk Management Sub-Committee.


Nobel Design Holdings Ltd, Annual General Meeting, Apr 28, 2017
Apr 12 17
Nobel Design Holdings Ltd, Annual General Meeting, Apr 28, 2017, at 17:30 Singapore Standard Time. Location: 16 Tai Seng Street, Level 7 Singapore Singapore Agenda: To consider the audited financial statements of the company for the financial year ended December 31, 2016; to declare a first and final (tax exempt one-tier) dividend of 0.52 cents per share for the financial year ended December 31, 2015; to approve the directors fees for the financial year ended December 31, 2016 and December 31, 2017; to re-elect retiring directors; to re-appoint Messrs Ernst & Young LLP as auditors of the company and to authorize the directors to fix their remuneration; to consider the authority to allot and issue shares; to consider the authority to grant options and issue shares under the Nobel Employee Share Option Scheme; and to transact any other matters.








 












